node.title: World's first planetary defence spacecraft lifts off
node.alt: A blurry image of a spacecraft taking off in the night.
node.description: NASA's one-way mission to crash a spacecraft into an asteroid blasts off from California. The mission is to demonstrate the world's first planetary defence system by deflecting an asteroid from a potential doomsday collision with Earth.
node.content: ["NASA's one-way mission to crash a spacecraft into an asteroid has blasted off from California.", "This\u00a0mission is to demonstrate the world's first planetary defence system by deflecting an asteroid from a potential doomsday collision with Earth.", "The so-called DART spacecraft soared into the night sky from the Vandenberg US Space Force Base, about 150 miles north-west of Los Angeles.", "The spacecraft will spend the next\u00a010 months travelling to the\u00a0target asteroid.", "More to come."]
